cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of high peak-to-mean envelope power ratio (PMEPR) in MC-CDMA system and proposes a new optimal ZCCS with larger set size to address the issue. This falls under the domain of information theory.
2. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper proposes a new code construction method for MC-CDMA system to support a large number of users with low PMEPR. This is relevant to the field of communication and networking.
3. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design and optimization of a system (MC-CDMA) using complementary codes. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new code construction method for MC-CDMA system, which is relevant to the field of networking and internet architecture.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a direct construction method for generating ZCCS for MC-CDMA system, which involves the use of Boolean functions. This falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms.
